  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the guidelines for a first offense of this magnitude with partial repayment generally warrant a short period of incarceration rather than a lengthy prison sentence. The outburst by the spectator is irrelevant to the legal merits of the case and does not influence the judicial determination of an appropriate sentence. Considering the mitigating factor of the lack of a prior criminal record and the partial restitution, a period of 6 months serves as a sufficient punitive and rehabilitative measure.",
  "verdict": 6
}
